  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "dy3Fm2Mos2vavNvwfCz0VQ0gdZ0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## What shipped\n\nChat can now share documents with the same fidelity as the Settings-level share flow.\n\n- **Document-share attachment type** - `DocumentShareAttachment` plus `DocumentShareCard` rendering.\n- **Adapter method** - `shareDocumentInChat` builds the bundle via the unified `buildDriveShareBundle`, performs the ACT upload and delivers via PSS.\n- **Composer share-document button + picker modal** - `document-share-picker.tsx` provides a drive selector, multi-select of documents, and a caption.\n- **Parity with Settings-share** - same bundle shape, full op history (including unflushed ops), original signer preserved.\n\n## Why it matters\n\nSharing in chat no longer loses authorship or history relative to the Settings share path, so chat is now a legitimate distribution surface for collaborative documents rather than a lossy broadcast channel.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
